        <name>get_injection_data</name>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Get the injection data of the plugin. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>The values returned from this method will be injected to Pin as environment variables. This method may be NULL.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>In Pin 4.0 beta, if <ref refid="structIRPCPlugin_1a8a8ebf74cc46bd403d655dbf4e632856" kindref="member">IRPCPlugin::get_injection_data</ref> is not NULL, it will be called but the returned data will not be injected to Pin.</para>
</simplesect>
<parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">self</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>A pointer to the plugin</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>A string of KEY=VALUE pairs with semicolon delimiter </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
