        <definition>t_rpc_message_schema const*(* IRPCPlugin::get_rpc_schema) (IPindPlugin *self, t_rpc_id rpcId)</definition>
        <argsstring>)(IPindPlugin *self, t_rpc_id rpcId)</argsstring>
        <name>get_rpc_schema</name>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Get the schema for the given id if supported by the plugin. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This method is called to retrieve an RPC schema when pind considers the plugin for processing an RPC request. This method must be set and may not be NULL.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">self</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>A pointer to the plugin </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">rpcId</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>RPC request ID</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>RPC message schema for the specified RPC request identified by <emphasis>rpcId</emphasis> if and only if the plugin supports this <emphasis>rpcId</emphasis>, NULL otherwise. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
